<p>The city is located on the northern coast of Colombia at a point where its rivers—the Magdalena and Cauca—intersect. It lies between the Caribbean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean, north of Santa Marta and south of Cartagena. The city has been officially recognized as an urban center (city) since 1917 by national law, but it had previously been considered a town since 1832 by presidential decree.</p>

